                              Solar panels. Source: VnExpress
                            </div>
                          </div>
                        </li>
                      
                      <li>Reducing Plastic Waste Vietnam is one of the five countries responsible for more than half of the plastic waste that ends up in the world's oceans. As a student, I can advocate for reducing plastic use and proper waste management practices to minimize environmental pollution</li> 
                      </ol>
                      In conclusion, addressing climate change in Vietnam I believe it requires considering the country's geography and economy and every citizen to have sense of cooperation as well as awareness to climate change. Solutions such as mangrove conservation, promoting sustainable tourism, adoption of renewable energy sources, and reducing plastic waste can help improve the country's environmental resilience and mitigate the impact of climate-related events.
                       
                      </p>
                      <p style="text-align:right;">- Hoang Pham Bao Tran _Sandbox JTC</p>
