                <div class="row">
                  <div class="col-lg-12 details order-2 order-lg-1">
                    <h3>APPLYING AI TO PREVENT CLIMATE CHANGE</h3>
                    <p class="fst-italic">
                    <span style="margin-left: 25px;"> That </span>is not just a dream, but a goal, a future is aiming for: a verdant hue, a lovely clean earth, a nice air entering your lungs, an air without harmful fumes, without the scorching sun's rays, but an ambient blue everywhere you walk. None of us prefers to breathe in smoke emanating from the factory every single time they go outside, emissions burning garbage, or trapped among the sea of people and vehicles, sirens blaring across the road. No one enjoys living in a flood situation, business is sluggish, another individual goes missing, or catastrophic weather conditions occur.
                    
                    <div>But what we humans don't want is occurring right now, every minute of every second; just a few minutes ago, a baby in Yen Bai was washed away, and a 9-year-old in Van Yen was also terrified when a storm followed by flooding took his life. Previously, a faulty sewer overflowed the Dong Ta Phoi factory, sweeping away many dwellings caused by landslides. </div>
                    
                    
                    <div class="image-holder-article-left">
                      <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/GiangSandbox/climatechange/main/img/thu-giang/flood-vietnam.png?raw=true" width = "300px">
                      <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/GiangSandbox/climatechange/main/img/thu-giang/drought-vietnam.png?raw=true" width = "300px">
                    </div>
                    
                    
                    <span>A row of cars became stranded in Hanoi's Soc Son area. Vietnam is one of the top five countries in the world in terms of vulnerability to climate change, thus the key issue now is... how to overcome, to tackle climate change, catastrophic weather?</span>
                    <span>	As it is known that climate change is caused by vehicles that emit greenhouse gases, with science now, many people have changed to electric cars instead of using petrol cars, switching to walking, driving. cycling to promote health as well as reduce greenhouse gas emissions.</span>

                    
                    
                    <span>Getting rid of coal burning is a challenging problem to address today since there are so many common commodities manufactured from this fuel that are used for both people mobility and cargo transportation. According to the International Energy Agency, coal is also the substrate that provides a source of electrical energy consumed globally. But it is also a highly dangerous adversary for the environment, and owing to research, many individuals have accepted other safer environmental solutions wherever feasible. For instance, utilising biodiesel, wind energy, solar energy, and so on. Plastic is created from oil, and the extraction and refining processes transform the oil into a shockingly high-carbon plastic. Because plastic takes a long time to degrade in nature, many people burn it, resulting in the release of hazardous pollutants. Plastics use is anticipated to expand so quickly that generation and disposal of plastics will account for 17% of the global carbon budget by 2050. So, what is the answer to this problem? That is, we must limit our usage of plastic in order to reduce waste while prioritising plastic recycling. Furthermore, please give precedence to items created from alternative materials that decompose quickly to replace plastic. While breeders talk a lot about vitamins, protein, fat, ... in meat, fish, shrimp that we use every day. It is also apparent that they are all essential nutrients for the body. However, this is only true if we consume the proper quantity. That implies you may drastically cut your daily meat and fish consumption while remaining fully healthy. Above all, in terms of environmental considerations, the cattle business emits hazardous gases that contribute to the greenhouse effect. Eating a lot of veggies is also a wonderful solution!~ Make your house or room more private by having soundproof and insulated doors, which may cut your heating and cooling expenditures by more than 25%. Simply setting the high temperature to 2 degrees higher in winter and lower than 2 degrees in summer may save around 2 tonnes of CO2 each year.

                    </span>
                    <span>With the current school age, if I can contribute to climate change, I will change myself from everyday things such as throwing trash in the right place, recycling unwanted items, limit the use of plastic bags, plastic waste, plant green trees, limit the use of air conditioners and heaters, turn off the power when not in use because a large part of electricity comes from the burning of buildings. fossil fuels, environmental protection propaganda, participating in movements, not using products from wild animals, ... If expanded further, I want to contribute more than that. I'll ask the government to make stricter laws to protect forests, protect the sea, and government incentives to reduce emissions. The government can use a number of incentives to influence the conduct of individuals (and organisations). Carbon pricing, such as a carbon tax, mandates businesses and individuals to pay taxes for their carbon footprint. Individuals may be induced to switch to electric automobiles via tax breaks. Participate in school or community environmental groups or organisations that encourage conservation, recycling, and long-term sustainability. Local eco-friendly projects, such as tree planting, cleaning, and anti-single-use plastics campaigns, should be promoted. If such a group or organisation does not already exist, consider creating one to engage your coworkers in the battle against climate change.</span>
                    <span>That is why I aspire to be an AI scientist (Artificial Intelligence). I want to contribute more parts like water purifier, AI (reaction - basic type) to find out which vegetables are suitable to grow in this environment, and program a website to measure pollution index from there, which can offer the most suitable solutions. Most people will rush to the store to buy air conditioners and refrigerators when the temperature is 40 degrees Celsius or higher than usual in order to escape the heat. However, because these appliances use electricity which is made from coal to operate and also produce heat which also affects the environment , increasing temperature differences not only doesn't help anything, but also accelerates climate change. In order to keep the water clean while still having a cooling effect similar to an air conditioner, happy in 24 °C, I want to create a system to cool the water from which it travels throughout the city. I want to use artificial intelligence (AI) computer science to develop a virtual Vietnam, mimic it, and then green the buildings in that virtual Vietnam which is metaverse ( a concept defined by Facebook, it is a virtual world that people can experience in many different roles like the real world. Here each person, object, or thing can be an incarnation in separate virtual spaces and worlds, and can play different roles in many different spaces ) to turn the land green, more environmentally friendly water and then giving people real experience, bringing it to the state government and requesting for the construction of the country, because growing trees helps with flood resistance and absorbs less sunlight than concrete as well as capable of purifying the air, and further is the planting of plants that can not only be planted in the ground but can also be grown on high, many plants including vines are still able to reach over the high buildings to the blue sky. I'll utilise artificial intelligence to gauge environmental pollution levels so I can develop effective responses, as well as to detect storm, flood, and landslip warning signals so I can alert everyone in the nation to prepare mentally and physically in order to reduce the amount of missing persons and fatalities brought on by extreme weather occurrences.</span>

                    <p style="text-align:right;">- Nguyen Thu Giang _Sandbox JTC</p>
                  </p>
